# 04 - PoisonSeed Recruitment-themed Phishing

## Intro

We will take an intel lead for recruitment-themed phishing. We will do additional intel collections. We will action the intel by first searching Any Run submissions for sessions that analyze the phishing emails. We will extract the domain indicator from the Any Run session. I ran the domain in urlscan. We will access the urlscan task, and then we will analyze it and identify the pattern. We will action the pattern (the page title), and identify other domain indicators.
## Intel Lead

The intel lead is a post from Lontze (@lontze7) stating there's a massive Google Careers phishing campaign that is ongoing.
https://x.com/lontze7/status/1973996772704825351

![](data:image/png;base64,)

I used additional intel from Validin [https://x.com/ValidinLLC/status/1974127562201657674] stating Will (@BushidoToken) had a Gist [https://gist.github.com/BushidoUK/e44625b0439024730f7e233bc9eeb85a]. I ended up using Will's other Gist [https://gist.github.com/BushidoUK/daf14c2066cfd530114d9227cf85c328] because it included the following key info:
- The sender's domain ended with`[@]s12[.]y[.]mc[.]salesforce[.]com`
- The embedded link used the`cl[.]s12[.]exct[.]net` domain
	- This is key info that we'll use to find Any Run sessions. 

Review all the references that were included before we move forward.

## Identify a Pattern

I went to urlscan and ran this task so that we can identify a pattern [https://urlscan.io/result/019a315f-83af-7221-93e3-aab1dda727d3/]. Here's the snip below. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Perform the Pivot

We will pivot on the page title. It is "Find the right job type for you | Robert Half". This should be a good pivot because it's a lure for Adidas, but it has another company name "Robert Half" in the title. It may indicate the threat actor will use the same page title for other lures.

Here's the urlscan query and the direct link:

page.title:"Find the right job type for you | Robert Half"
https://urlscan.io/search/#page.title%3A%22Find%20the%20right%20job%20type%20for%20you%20%7C%20Robert%20Half%22

Here's the result.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The first scan task is the one I just did. We'll take a look at the next one [https://urlscan.io/result/019a30b1-4913-70fd-ab66-fd90f28981e9]. In the snip below, we can see that it matches. It is great because it is a Nike lure. It is great because the pivot will find lures from multiple brands.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Validation

We validate that the lure page is structurally the same. The only difference is that this page pretends to be Nike instead of an Adidas. These are created in bulk, and it is highly-likely that there may not be external validation sources.
